(138, 'App\\Models\\DataSetting', 86, 'en', 'privacy_policy', '<p>This Privacy Policy (the &quot;Policy&quot;) outlines the guidelines for the gathering, using, disclosing, and safeguarding of your personal data when you use the Yehlo mobile application or the Yehlo website (together, the &quot;Yehlo Platform&quot;). These are provided by U Quick E-Commerce Private Limited (the &quot;Company,&quot; &quot;Yehlo,&quot; &quot;we,&quot; &quot;us,&quot; and &quot;our&quot;), a private business registered in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Yehlo Platform user is referred to by the terms &quot;you&quot; and &quot;your.&quot; Any services provided by Yehlo, whether through the Yehlo Platform or not, are referred to as &quot;Services.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before using the Yehlo Platform or providing Yehlo with any personal information, please read this Policy. The Terms of Use should be read in conjunction with this Policy, which is an integral component of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Your Agreement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree and consent to the collection, transfer, use, storage, disclosure, and sharing of your information as specified and collected by us in compliance with this Policy by using the Yehlo Platform and the Services. Please do not use or access the Yehlo Platform if you disagree with the Policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>CHANGES IN POLICY</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This Policy may occasionally be updated; if so, updates will be noted on this page. If we make any important changes to this policy, we will try to notify you as soon as possible. For example, we may post a notice prominently on the Yehlo Platform or send an email to the address we have on file. If relevant legislation requires it, we will also get your consent. If we publish or notify you of changes to this Policy, your continuing use of our Services will be deemed your assent to the new Policy, to the extent allowed by applicable law.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>HYPERLINKS ABOARD SECTION</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There can be links to external websites on the Yehlo Platform. This Policy does not apply to any personal information about you that may be collected while using these websites. Any website accessible through links on the Yehlo Platform is not within the control or responsibility of Yehlo, and Yehlo disclaims all liability for the actions and content of such websites. Any information you choose to submit to any of our service providers or staff that we do not require you to disclose to us or any of our service providers under this Policy will not be covered by this Policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>DATA THAT WE GATHER FROM YOU</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Session and Persistent Cookies</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Device Information: We may collect information about your devices used to access our services, or we may use third-party plugins to do so. This information includes the hardware models, operating systems and versions, software, file names and versions, preferred languages, unique device identifiers, advertising identifiers, serial numbers, device motion information, mobile network information, installed applications on the device, and phone state. Our goal is to enhance your app experience and provide stability to our services. These plugins will either directly collect or receive the information gathered in this way, and it may be utilized to enhance the features and/or content of the services that are provided to you. Mobile device IDs may be used by analytics businesses to monitor how you use the Yehlo Platform;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cookie-based</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Yehlo Platform and our affiliated third parties may employ similar files or technologies, such as &quot;flash cookies,&quot; pixel tags, web beacons, mobile device IDs, and cookies, to gather and save data about how you use the Services and other websites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cookies are little files that websites, apps, online media, and ads save on your browser or device. We employ cookies and related technologies for the following purposes:</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>- Verifying user identity;<br />\r\n- Preserving user preferences and settings;<br />\r\n- Assessing the popularity of content;<br />\r\n- Managing the delivery and evaluation of advertising campaigns;<br />\r\n- Examining traffic patterns and trends on the website, and in general, comprehending the online habits and interests of users interacting with our services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>A pixel tag, also known as a web beacon or clear GIF, is a tiny graphic with a unique identifier that is imperceptibly embedded on a webpage (or in an email or online advertisement). It can be used to track and count actions such as clicks or impressions on advertisements, activity on the webpage, and access cookies that are stored on users&#39; computers. Pixel tags are used by us to gauge how well-liked our different pages, features, and services are. Web beacons may also be used in newsletters or email correspondence to track open rates and for further analytical purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We might also permit outside parties to monitor and report on the effectiveness of our advertisements, deliver ads across the Internet on our behalf, and measure and analyze our audience. When you visit the Yehlo Platform and use our services, as well as when you visit other websites and services, these organizations may use cookies, web beacons, SDKs, and other technologies to identify your device.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>USES OF YOUR INFORMATION - We use the data we collect for the following purposes, among others:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. To provide, personalize, maintain, and improve our products and services, such as enabling deliveries and other services and enabling features to personalize your Yehlo account;<br />\r\nii. To fulfill our obligations resulting from any contracts we may have with you and to give you the pertinent information and services;<br />\r\niii. To manage and improve the security of our Yehlo Platform and for internal operations, such as statistical analysis, testing, troubleshooting.<br />\r\niv. To enlighten you about services we think are comparable to those you may be interested in, are now using, or have inquired about. If you are a registered user, we will send you information about these services via electronic mail, SMS, phone call, or other internet-based instant messaging systems;<br />\r\nv. To comprehend our users (what they do, what features they prefer, how they use them, etc.); to enhance the features and content of our Services (e.g., by tailoring content to your interests); to process and fulfill your transactions; to present promotional offers; to offer customer support; to process and address your inquiries;<br />\r\nvi. To compile and analyze data and reports regarding our user base and service usage trends, as well as to carry out research on them; viii. To gauge the success of the ads we show you and other users and to show you appropriate ads.<br />\r\nix. To monitor the status of our customers&#39; orders or the delivery progress if you are a delivery partner, merchant, or partner restaurant.<br />\r\nx. To do scholarly research alongside academic collaborators.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes mentioned above, we may mix information we get from third parties with information you provide to us and information we gather about you. Furthermore, we may utilize third-party web analytics tools or other methods to anonymize and/or de-identify information we acquire from you through the Services. Therefore, this Policy does not limit our use or disclosure of aggregated and/or de-identified information, and we are free to use and disclose it to others as we see fit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We examine the Yehlo Platform&#39;s log files, which might include information on IP addresses, browser types and languages, ISPs, referrals, app crashes, the websites and applications that are browsed and exited, operating systems, date/time stamps, and clickstream data. This aids in website administration, user behavior analysis, product and service improvement, and the collection of demographic data about our user base as a whole.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>DISPLAY AND DISSEMINATION OF YOUR DATA</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your information that we gather from you might be shared for the following reasons: Regarding Service Providers: In order to support our company, we might disclose your information to our consultants, vendors, marketing partners, research firms, and other service providers or business partners, like payment processing businesses. To help us evaluate and optimize how you use our services, to process and collect payments, or to send you emails and messages or push notifications to your devices, for instance, your information may be shared with other parties. Additionally, we might hire outside companies to help us with other tasks like survey administration and sweepstakes setup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Partner Vendors: When you use the Yehlo Platform to request Grocery delivery, your information is shared with both us and the Vendors you can select to order from. We give your information to that Store Vendor in a way that makes processing your online order as easy as if you had placed your order with the Vendor Store directly. Yehlo might text you about the order&#39;s delivery status if you give them your mobile number.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Academic Partners: In order to conduct academic research, we might disclose your information to our academic partners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To prevent or investigate crime: We may disclose this information to governmental organizations or other businesses that support us when we are: Required by law to do so, or acting in good faith in response to court orders and procedures; orspotting and stopping identity theft, fraud, service misuse, and other unlawful activities before they happen or could happen;answering allegations pertaining to infringement of a third party&#39;s intellectual property rights by an advertisement, posting, or other content; In the event of a claim or dispute pertaining to your use of our Services, or in the event that we are required by law to disclose or share your personal data in order to enforce our Terms of Use and other agreements, policies, or to defend the rights, property, or safety of the Company, our customers, or others. This involves sharing data with other businesses and organizations in order to detect fraud and lower credit risk.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Internal Use: Any existing or potential member of our &quot;Group&quot; (as defined below) or affiliates may receive your information from us for internal business purposes. Any entity that an individual controls, is controlled by, or shares control with, whether directly or indirectly, is referred to as a &quot;Group&quot; in reference to that individual. According to the Companies Act of 1956 and the Companies Act of 2013, respectively, a natural person is referred to as a &quot;Relative&quot; in this context.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regarding Advertisers and Advertising Networks: We might collaborate with other parties, such network advertisers, to display ads on the Yehlo Platform as well as on other websites and media (like social networking sites). These third parties may measure the efficacy of their advertisements and tailor you with personalized advertising material by using cookies, JavaScript, web beacons (including clear GIFs), Flash LSOs, and other tracking technologies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Yehlo Platform does not allow you to opt out of advertising, however you can do so for a large portion of interest-based advertising on other websites and through other ad networks (such as DoubleClick Ad Exchange, Facebook Audience Network, and Google AdSense). Go to www.aboutads.info/choices for additional information. By opting out, you will stop seeing tailored advertisements from third-party ad networks that are based on your browsing history across various websites and online services. It is possible that your opt-out will no longer work if you clear cookies or switch devices.to achieve the goal for which you give it.If we tell you and you agree to the sharing, we may disclose your information in ways other than those specified in this policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>DATA SECURITY MARKERS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We have put in place the necessary security and technical safeguards to protect the data we collect.To safeguard the sensitive personal data you have submitted, we use vault and tokenization services from outside service providers. Regarding our payment gateway, payment processing, vault and tokenization services, and other third-party service providers, they comply with the payment card industry standard (often referred to as PCI compliant service providers). It is recommended that you avoid transmitting your entire credit/debit card number via unencrypted online channels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please be advised that there is some degree of security involved in information transfer over the internet. We cannot ensure the security of your data transmitted through the Yehlo Platform, despite our best efforts to secure it. We shall attempt to prevent unauthorised access to your information by implementing stringent physical, electronic, and administrative precautions after we receive it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Choose not to</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to receive emails from Yehlo when you create an account. It is not possible to choose not to receive certain administrative, service, or legal notices from Yehlo, but you can log in to modify your email settings or unsubscribe from commercial emails by following the instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you would like your data to be destroyed or would like to revoke your consent for us to use and disclose your personal information as described in this Policy, please email&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"mailto:support@yehloapp.com\">support@yehloapp.com</a>&nbsp;</strong>. Please be aware that processing such requests may take some time. Your request will become effective after 5 (five) business days of our receiving it, after which we won&#39;t use your personal information for any further processing unless it&#39;s necessary for us to comply with the law. In the event that you withdraw your consent, we might not be able to provide you with some or all Services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Officer of Grievance and Yehlo Platform Safety Should you have any questions about how your information is processed or used in accordance with this Policy, send us an email at&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"mailto:support@yehloapp.com\">support@yehloapp.com</a>&nbsp;</strong>or send a letter to our Grievance Officer at the following address:</p>', NULL, NULL);
