(429, 'App\\Models\\Item', 39, 'en', 'description', 'Product description\r\n\r\nSamsung Galaxy F54 5G mobile was launched on 6th June 2023. The phone comes with a 120 Hz refresh rate 6.70-inch touchscreen display offering a resolution of 2400x1080 pixels (FHD+). Samsung Galaxy F54 5G is powered by an octa-core Samsung Exynos 1380 processor. It comes with 8GB of RAM. The Samsung Galaxy F54 5G runs Android 13 and is powered by a 6000mAh non-removable battery. The Samsung Galaxy F54 5G supports proprietary fast charging. As far as the cameras are concerned, the Samsung Galaxy F54 5G on the rear packs a triple camera setup featuring a 108-megapixel primary camera; an 8-megapixel camera, and a 2-megapixel camera. It has a single front camera setup for selfies, featuring a 32-megapixel sensor. The Samsung Galaxy F54 5G runs OneUI 5 is based on Android 13 and packs 256GB of inbuilt storage that can be expanded via microSD card (up to 1000GB). The Samsung Galaxy F54 5G is a dual-SIM mobile that accepts Nano-SIM and Nano-SIM cards. The Samsung Galaxy F54 5G measures 164.90 x 77.30 x 8.40mm (height x width x thickness) and weighs 199.00 grams. It was launched in Meteor Blue and Stardust Silver colours. Connectivity options on the Samsung Galaxy F54 5G include Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/ax, GPS, Bluetooth v5.30, USB Type-C, 4G (with support for Band 40 used by some LTE networks in India) , and 5G with active 4G on both SIM cards. Sensors on the phone include accelerometer, ambient light sensor, compass/ magnetometer, gyroscope, proximity sensor, and fingerprint sensor.', NULL, NULL),
